  "docs": {
    "sections": [
      {
        "kind": "summary",
        "title": "Summary",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Return the roots of a polynomial with coefficients given in p."
          },
          {
            "type": "directive",
            "name": "note",
            "body": "   This forms part of the old polynomial API. Since version 1.4, the\n   new polynomial API defined in `numpy.polynomial` is preferred.\n   A summary of the differences can be found in the\n   :doc:`transition guide </reference/routines.polynomials>`.",
            "raw": ".. note::\n   This forms part of the old polynomial API. Since version 1.4, the\n   new polynomial API defined in `numpy.polynomial` is preferred.\n   A summary of the differences can be found in the\n   :doc:`transition guide </reference/routines.polynomials>`."
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "The values in the rank-1 array `p` are coefficients of a polynomial.\nIf the length of `p` is n+1 then the polynomial is described by::"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "  p[0] * x**n + p[1] * x**(n-1) + ... + p[n-1]*x + p[n]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "parameters",
        "title": "Parameters",
        "items": [
          {
            "name": "p",
            "type": "array_like",
            "desc_blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Rank-1 array of polynomial coefficients."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "returns",
        "title": "Returns",
        "items": [
          {
            "name": "out",
            "type": "ndarray",
            "desc_blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "An array containing the roots of the polynomial."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "notes",
        "title": "Notes",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "The algorithm relies on computing the eigenvalues of the\ncompanion matrix [1]_."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "examples",
        "title": "Examples",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> import numpy as np\n>>> coeff = [3.2, 2, 1]\n>>> np.roots(coeff)\narray([-0.3125+0.46351241j, -0.3125-0.46351241j])"
          }
        ]
      },
